  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients after elective coronary artery bypass surgery, hemodynamically stable,
             without ischemic changes and / or complex arrhythmias on the electrocardiogram,
             between 45 and 75 years of age, who have performed the first surgery

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with decompensated heart failure; other associated surgery; presence of any
             comorbidity such as: unstable angina; sequel of stroke; photosensitivity; use of
             cardiac pacemaker; Diabetes mellitus (due to the negative effect of diabetes on wound
             healing).
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
